Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Bring a #large saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the gnocchi.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the @balsamic vinegar{12%ml}, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Set your dressing aside.

Lay the @salmon fillets{2}, skin-side down, onto a lined #baking tray{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Spread over the @pesto{32%g}.

Pop the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g} alongside the salmon. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

When the oven is hot, roast the salmon and tomatoes on the middle shelf until cooked through, ~{10-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish. The fish is cooked when opaque in the middle.

Meanwhile, when boiling, add the @gnocchi{300%g} to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until the gnocchi rise to the surface of the water, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{}. Drizzle with oil and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, pop the @serrano ham{2%slices} onto a baking tray and bake on the top shelf of your oven until crisp and golden, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Dry the (now empty) #saucepan{} and return to medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Once hot, add the garlic and cook, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @creme fraiche{75%g} and @water{75%ml} for the sauce. Bring to the boil and simmer until thickened slightly, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir the @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g}, @parmigiano reggiano{20%g}, roasted tomatoes and cooked gnocchi into the sauce. Bring to the boil and simmer until piping hot, ~{1%minute}. Remove from the heat.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Add a splash of water if it's a little thick.

When everything's ready, add the @wild rocket{40%g} to the dressing bowl and toss to coat.

Share the gnocchi between your bowls.

Top with the pesto salmon. Break the serrano ham into shards and scatter over.

Serve the balsamic rocket salad in a #bowl{} alongside. Enjoy!